â”Œâ”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”
â”‚                                   QVerse End-to-End Flow                                    â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 1. User inputs a query via Genie UI (FastAPI endpoint triggered).                          â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 2. Request is passed through JWT authentication middleware.                                â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 3. `Flow.validate_user_request()` validates session, logs history, loads config.           â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 4. `Flow.fetch_db_details()` connects to Teradata or configured DB using secure credentials.â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 5. `Flow.thinkforge_search()` or `Flow.ask_thinkforge()` checks if similar NLQ exists.     â”‚
â”‚     - If cache hit â†’ use cached SQL.                                                       â”‚
â”‚     - Else â†’ use reasoning trace + LLM to create SQL.                                      â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 6. If cache fails, `Catalog_lookup.generate_catalog_query()` retrieves vector-based contextâ”‚
â”‚     - Uses PGVector + TF-IDF over table metadata and business rules.                       â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 7. `Agents.generate_query()` sends metadata context to LLM to generate SQL + follow-ups.   â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 8. `Flow.validate_response()` ensures query is syntactically valid and retry up to 3x      â”‚
â”‚     - Auto-corrects SQL via LLM if execution fails.                                        â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚ 9. Final query is executed on DB. Results are captured and formatted using Pandas.         â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚10. `Flow.execute_query()` calls LLM again to generate:                                     â”‚
â”‚     - Recommended visualizations (chart type + fields)                                     â”‚
â”‚     - Summary or insights from result set                                                  â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â”‚11. Final output returned to UI:                                                            â”‚
â”‚     - SQL, Data, Visuals, Summary, Follow-ups, Metadata                                    â”‚
â”‚                                                                                            â”‚
â””â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”€â”˜


